observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Management:
a) Formulate documented/written guidelines or uniform policy and procedures in the engagement of JO and COS workers to ensure that the hiring process is systematic and include the standard qualifications based on the work to be assigned;
b) Execute contract of service specially for consultants that defines the technical knowledge and experience required, tasks and duties to be accomplished and its desired deliverables which are time bound;
c) Direct the HRMO together with the department heads/ immediate supervisors to ensure that job orders and COS accurately reflect a quantified and accurate actual work performed and ensure that these are the actual deliverables stated in their contracts;
d) Conduct regular assessment of the Manpower Complement of the LGU to determine whether the hiring of a permanent employee is more beneficial than the periodic hiring of job orders or COS; and
e) Strengthen their measures towards curbing unnecessary expenses and instead, maximize the use of the funds to some programs that support the local projects of the Municipality.

Management Comments:
The Management agreed with our recommendations and agreed to revisit and review the accomplishment of the job orders and consultants, and make the necessary revisions with their contracts regarding their deliverables and accomplishment reports. They also informed the Audit Team that the basketball players are representatives of the LGU and have been accorded support by the Management but the LGU will comply with the prescribed guidelines and procedures.

Likewise, the submitted guidelines in the hiring of Contract of Service/Job Order personnel are for CY 2025 implementation and not attributable to policies and guidelines of previous years subject to audit.

