We recommended that Management require the:
43) Municipal Treasurer in coordination with the Municipal Assessor to come up with a correct Statement of Real Property Tax Receivables (SRPTR) starting from CY 2019 and onward; 
44) Municipal Treasurer to take extra effort in collecting RPT/SET from delinquent taxpayers; update the RPT Tax system or evaluate the effectiveness and efficiency of the RPT Tax and consider replacing or upgrading the system; and verify the correctness of the SRPTR before furnishing the same to the Accounting and Auditor’s Office.

We recommended that the Management:

Require the General Services Officer (GSO) to prepare the Summary of Supplies and Materials Issued (SSMI) based on the Requisition and Issue Slips (RIS), at least on a monthly basis, to be submitted to the Municipal Accountant as basis for the preparation of the Journal Entry Voucher (JEV) to record issuances of inventories from stock;

Further, the GSO prepare and maintain stock cards for each type of inventory, with complete information/data to facilitate verification receipts, issuances and balances of inventories on hand; 

Require the GSO and the Municipal Accountant to reconcile their records, at least, on a quarterly basis to ensure accuracy of the balances of the inventory accounts;

Provide an adequate stockroom to safely keep all procured stocks of the LGU so that inventories are only issued to end-users when needed; and

Subject to availability of funds, augment the manpower of the GSO so that there will be a personnel in-charged with the recording, monitoring, and safekeeping of the inventories of the Municipality.

We recommended that Management require the Municipal Accountant to:
Return to the concerned source agencies the unutilized balance of the fund transfer wherein the agreement requires the return thereof;
Revert to Government Equity the balances of fund transfers in the nature of financial assistance and subsidy wherein the agreement does not mention of the disposition of the unused balance and that future utilization thereof will be subject to the usual accounting, auditing and budgeting laws, rules and regulations;
Retain special purpose funds; and
Clean the books of accounts, in accordance with the provisions of COA Circular No. 2016-005 in order to present fairly the Liability accounts in the financial statements.

We recommended that Management instruct the Property Officer:
To prepare and submit the Property Inventory Form (PIF) to GIF, GSIS, and to the Auditor, in compliance with COA Circular 2018-002 and, in coordination with the Municipal Engineering Office, ensure that all the insurable properties and assets of the Municipality are included in the said listing;
Ensure that sufficient appropriation is made to cover the Insurance Expense for all insurable properties;
To immediately secure insurance coverage for the buildings and other insurable properties not yet insured from GIF, GSIS; and
To always ensure that the insurance coverage of the insurable properties and assets of the Municipality are promptly renewed every year and that adequate insurance coverage are secured on the assets to provide the Municipality protection and indemnification for any damage caused to the assets due to fire, earthquake, storm or other calamities.

