Subject to availability of funds, augment the manpower of the GSO so that there will be personnel charged with the recording, monitoring, and safekeeping of the inventories of the Municipality.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive require:

The Municipal Accountant to record all purchases of Supplies and Materials under the perpetual inventory method to ensure proper accounting and promote better control in the receipt and issuance of Supplies and Materials;

The Property Officer to maintain updated perpetual inventory subsidiary records for all kinds of inventories. At the end of each month, she shall prepare the monthly Summary of Supplies and Materials Issued, a copy of which shall be furnished the Municipal Accountant for recording as well as the Audit Team;

The Property Officer, at the end of each semester, shall conduct physical inventory, in coordination with the concerned department/office, of all unused Supplies and Materials and shall prepare a consolidated report thereon and furnish the Municipal Accountant a copy thereof; 

The Municipal Accountant to take up the necessary adjustment, if any, in the respective inventory and expense accounts for Supplies and Materials based on the consolidated inventory report provided by the Property Office; and

The MSWD Officer to fast track the submission of the Relief Distribution Sheets for the welfare goods distributed containing the names of recipients and their signatures.

We commended Management for its SWM accomplishments.  Further, we recommended that Management: 

Strictly adhere to the approved 10-Year ESWMP  to ensure its sustainability, effectiveness and relevance in relation to local and international progress in the area of Solid Waste Management;

Properly supervise the maintenance of all Material Recovery Facilities in all the Barangays of the Municipality to achieve its purpose of ensuring the cleanliness of the entire community.

We recommended the following:

Management to constitute an Inventory Committee headed by the Municipal Engineer that should conduct the inventory of the local roads under the jurisdiction of the Municipality.  A Report on the Physical count of the Road Networks System should be prepared copy furnished the Municipal Accountant and the MGSO;

The MGSO to: (b.1) Render a Report on Local Road Network and Road Map; and, (b.2) Keep a complete and updated Local Road Network Property Card (LRNPCs) for all roads and its components;

The Municipal Engineer to provide the Municipal Accountant and the MGSO with the complete description and cost segregation of road components for road projects; and, 

The Municipal Accountant to prepare the JEV to reconcile the local road network account and its components and, henceforth, prepare and maintain the corresponding Local Road Network Ledger Cards (LRNLCs); keep and maintain subsidiary records for roads and road components for every road network and prepare a lapsing schedule for the computation of the depreciation for each component at the end of the year.

We recommended that Management:

Formulate or update land use plan, in consultation with the concerned sectors in the community. Seek the assistance of local official or field officer of National Government Agency concerned operating in the LGU;

Consider concerned personnel to attend trainings and seminars related to the preparation of CLUP;

Strengthen internet connection needed in gathering information and secure back-up copy of all the output made; and

Appoint/designate personnel with computer technical knowhow to facilitate the preparation of CLUP.

